Professor Robert's group

Robert Hoehndorf

Assistant Professor of Computer Science at King Abdullah University of Science and Technology

He is the principal investigator of the Bio-Ontology Research Group. His research focuses on artificial intelligence, knowledge representation, biomedical informatics and ontology. He conceived the study for Bio2Vec.

Senay Kafkas

Research Scientist in the Bio-Ontology Research Group

She received her Ph.D. in Computer Engineering from the Eastern Mediterranean University and previously worked as a Text Mining Specialist at the European Bioinformatics Group in the United Kingdom. She indexed the data and metadata for this project and drafted the manuscript.

Maxat Kulmanov

Ph.D. student in the Bio-Ontology Research Group

He designed the web interface and generated the PPI network embeddings.

Mona Alshahrani

Ph.D. student in the Bio-Ontology Research Group

She generated the knowledge graph embeddings.
